{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/1692","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/1692/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/1692/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/1692/events","html_url":"https://github.com/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/1692","id":6106920,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2MTA2OTIw","number":1692,"title":"Bug in DB_driver.php method display_error()","user":{"login":"bolemeus","id":1689125,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2ODkxMjU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1689125?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus","html_url":"https://github.com/bolemeus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bolemeus/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2012-08-08T16:25:27Z","updated_at":"2012-10-05T14:06:10Z","closed_at":"2012-10-05T14:06:10Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I noticed a bug in the method display_error() whilst looking for a way to generate neat error messages using the display_error() method.\n\nI figured the best way to do this way to look how codeigniter handles errors itself.\n\nI noticed that the backtrace is being evaluated to check which file and line-number is the culprit for the error, but I also noticed that database errors always show me the DB_driver.php class with line-number 330.\n\nThis shouldn't be the error found according to the condition:\n\nisset($call['file']) && strpos($call['file'], BASEPATH.'database') === FALSE //line 1180\n\nI found that the method strpos($call['file'], BASEPATH.'database') always returns false on the first call of the trace because $call['file'] and BASEPATH are formatted differently.\n\nprint_r($call['file']) returns:\nC:\\www\\test\\frontend\\system\\database\\DB_driver.php\n\nwhilst print_r(BASEPATH) returns\nC:/www/test/frontend/system/\n\nThis is a slashes vs backslashes issue...\n\nreplacing line 1180 by...\n\nif (isset($call['file']) && strpos($call['file'], FCPATH.SYSDIR.'\\'.'database') === FALSE)\n\nseems to do the trick. It now shows the file causing the error...\n","closed_by":{"login":"narfbg","id":1058011,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNTgwMTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1058011?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg","html_url":"https://github.com/narfbg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/narfbg/rece